@node eng_plot "The Story So Far..."

Engelbrecht "Nebu" Chadnessar was born in a small village outside the city of
Zürich, Switzerland, in the year 1887. His parents, Jan and Ida Chadnessar,
were famous for their good cheese, which they brewed themselves, so they hoped
their son would also become a cheese maker.
  Such was not the case. When he was six years old, young Engelbrecht began to
take interest in detective work. By 1895, he had managed to solve his greatest
case so far: where the missing cats of the village shoemaker, Mr. Nicholas
Ifta, had gone. Engelbrecht got his pay from Mr. Ifta and was celebrated at
home by his parents.
  When he was going to sleep, a spectral figure appeared beside his bed. "Do
not be alarmed", it said. "I have heard of your detective abilities, and I have
a job for you." Engelbrecht was becoming interested in the figure's story. The
figure went on: "In my dimension, I created a few hundred magical skulls, but
due to my inability to control my magical creations, I spilt them all over the
place. I want you to devise a way to get rid of them."
  Now Engelbrecht realised that the figure indeed had a job for him. "To aid
you, I've placed 'power cubes' in the places I spilt the skulls. Also you will
receive pay for every skull you get rid of, and can have a good time in my
dimension." "What is my ultimate reward for this job?" asked Engelbrecht. "I
offer you eternal peace in the Ocean of Time!" said the figure, somewhat
proudly. "Sounds cool", said Engelbrecht. "I accept!"
  The figure cast a magical spell that turned Engelbrecht into a shiny metal
ball ("for easy mobility in my dimension", said the figure) and a portal
appeared, whisking Engelbrecht into a place he had never seen before. "Good
luck, young man", said the figure, "you're going to need it!"

    Now this is where YOU come in. Your job is to guide the Ball (previously
    known as Engelbrecht Chadnessar) among all the levels, and collect all
    the magical skulls you find. Good luck!
@endnode
@node eng_menu "I'll have the Chateubriand"

The main menu appears when you first start the game Cubical Worlds. It has
eight actions for you to perform:

    - Start game
Obviously you know what this one does.
    - Load a saved game (not available in @{"unregistered" link "eng_money"} version)
Load a situation file from disk, and begin playing from there.
    - Delete a file
You can use this to delete all kinds of files from disk, not just Cubical
Worlds saved games.
    - High Scores
Use this button to view the amazing @{"Top 1000" link "eng_highscores"} high scores list.
    - Game Information
Free memory, processor speed, time spent and so on.
    - Music
This allows you to select a music file for Cubical Worlds. The music has to be
in .abk format, the bank must be #3, and it must be the only bank in the file.
For starters, I have included the music "Voyager", composed by Hellraiser of
Triumph, for it was the music used in @{"Revolution!" link "eng_revolution"}
    - Print the High Scores
This button allows you to print the Top 1000 list either onto paper or into a
file on disk.
    - Quit
I'm not exactly sure what this button does. In fact it got there by mistake.
@endnode
@node eng_play "Hoi, let's play!"

Cubical Worlds consists of 40 levels (10 in the @{"unregistered" link "eng_money"} version), all of
which have the same overall design.
  In a level, there are a lot of blocks. These can be in a flat, 2D formation,
or be on layers on top of one another, in a 3D formation. All the layers are
shown together, viewed from above. Play the game to see what I mean.
  Your Ball moves on these cubes. It is subject to gravity, but fortunately
there are some lifts that help you go back up. Every level has two power cubes
and some magical skulls. You have to collect all skulls and then turn on both
power cubes simultaneously to proceed to the next level.
  Also, some levels have a Spider running along. This Spider can just run
clockwise or it can follow you. It is able to use most of the things on screen,
just like you.
  To move the Ball, use the joystick or cursor keys. Pressing Fire or Space
while standing on a lift will make the lift go up or down. And if you are in
Anti-Grav mode, pressing Fire or Space while on empty air will make you go
downwards. You cannot go upwards in this way.
  There are a lot of @{"objects" link "eng_objects"} on the blocks, which are documented in another
node.
@endnode
@node eng_objects "Objection!"

As you traverse through the levels in Cubical Worlds, you may find the
following objects:

    - Power Cubes.
These come in three forms: Green, Purple and Toggler. Touching a cube will
activate it, and its charge will slowly decrease as time passes.
    - Magical skulls.
These also come in three forms: Green, Purple and Black. Green and Purple
skulls can only be collected when a cube of the respective colour is active,
but Black skulls can be collected when any cube is active.
    - Lifts.
Stand on these gray arrow-blocks and press Fire or Space to move up or down.
    - Barriers.
These look like brown pyramids, and are impassable.
    - Magma.
Red hot stuff that is lethal to the touch.
    - Teleports.
These little yellow dots will whisk you or the Spider to a random place when
touched.
    - Ice.
When you step on ice, you will skid in the direction you moved until you
either hit something or get off the ice.
    - Fragile blocks.
Recognisable by the black dot pattern on them. Some of these can take two
steps before crumbling to nothing, others crumble straight after you step on
them.
    - Locks and keys.
You can collect keys, and open locks with them.

Some blocks can be transparent to show you what is underneath them.
@endnode
@node eng_shop "You name it, we've got it (we think)"

The Shop appears every time you complete a level. Here you can buy or sell
30 different items, each with its own price and purpose. Notice that there is
no separate money account in this game, you buy things with your score.
  Also on this screen, you can save your game to disk (not available in the
@{"unregistered" link "eng_money"} version), view game information or quit the game altogether.
  Although the 30 different items might seem a little mysterious to someone, I
will not document them in any way. See for yourself what they do. Cunning,
ain't I?
@endnode
@node eng_daleks "Eat your heart out, Dr. Who!"

The game Cubical Worlds includes a sub-game called Daleks, which is a lot like
the classic game called, um, Daleks. I will not tell you how to find this game.
See for yourself.
  Anyway, in this game, it's your job to destroy all the Daleks on its 30
levels. Use the numeric keypad to move your character, press 0 to use a bomb or
press Enter to teleport.
  And if you want to play a better version of Daleks, you can order the game
Super Daleks from me. See the @{"registration" link "eng_money"} node.
@endnode
@node eng_highscores "The All-Time Top 1000"

Wowza! This Highscore list is pretty big! The biggest Highscore list I have
seen in any other game is a Top 100 in TopHat Willy by Thermodynamics
Heikkinen of OverFlow Productions, but this game has 900 more places.
  Each time you play a game of Cubical Worlds, you will get to see the High
