@node help "Aunt Hjördis, your Agony Aunt"
Hello, all you pathetic little losers. It's Aunt Hjördis here, you know, the
old bit... erm... lady that listens to all your ridiculous problems. Without
further ado, let's move on to what we have today!

Q: I've got an IBM PC.
A: Don't worry. We all make mistakes.

Q: I've got an Atari ST.
A: Send it to me! I'll pay up to £100 or 1000.- FIM to get my hands on one! No,
   really, I will. I think. ··)

Q: The game won't start.
A: Check that you have sufficient memory, and the file CWData.abk is in place.

Q: The graphics seem a little, ahem, weird.
A: You're using an AGA Amiga. Press LeftAmiga-A until you get the correct
   graphics. It might take a couple of tries.

Q: The graphics still seem a little, ahem, weird.
A: Well who asked for your opinion anyway?

Q: The game says "Not available in unregistered version" whenever I try to load
   or save a game.
A: I'll let you have three guesses.

Q: But now the game says "The file is counterfeit" whenever I try to load a
   saved game.
A: Check that the file indeed is a saved game, and you haven't got your dirty
   little hands modifying it.

Q: I don't know my name.
A: Neither do I.

Q: The game won't break by pressing Control-C.
A: Ha ha! Just a little device to keep you playing the game longer! You'll just
   have to quit from the main menu,

Q: I can't manage a level.
A: Send JIPsoft some dosh and a disk, and he'll send you the solution and/or a
   saved game to help you.

Q: I want to have my own levels included in this game.
A: Send plans of them to JIPsoft, and he'll see what he can do.

Q: I don't like you.
A: Then that makes two of us.

Q: My music won't play.
A: Check that it is in .abk format, it is bank #3, and it is the only bank in
   the file.

Q: I'm the last question.
A: I'm the last answer.
@endnode

